<![CDATA[<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><div style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" style="" size="2" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px;"><br></span></font></div><div style="text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" style="" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Dear&nbsp;{!Contact.Salutation} {!Contact.LastName},</span></font></div><span lang="en-GB" style="text-align: start; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><div style="margin: 0px;"><br>Next Wednesday is World Children’s Day and marks the 30th anniversary of the United Nations Convention for the Rights of Children. We want to celebrate Unicef’s excellent work in protecting the rights of children all over the world. It is important that every student in BSY knows their rights and is aware of the global issues surrounding children’s rights. We ask that the students go blue for Unicef and wear blue clothing (not their uniform) to school on 20th November. We have many activities to celebrate World Children’s Day, such as students taking over school for an hour- including the management team and school social media, a giant petition to protect children’s rights, blue specialties in the canteen and a World Children’s Day selfie booth.<br><br>Thank you. <br>Beat wishes,</div><div style="margin: 0px;"><br><br>Jessica Willmott<br><br></div><div style="margin: 0px;">Year 2B Teacher<br>BSY Unicef Coordinator</div><div style="margin: 0px;"><br></div></font></span></div><div style="text-align: left;"><p class="MsoNormal" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;"><font size="2" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" style="">The British School Yangon</font></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;"><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);" size="2">www.britishschoolyangon.org</font></p></div></div>]]></td>
